edu.cmu.sei.arche.vo
Class RelationshipVO

java.lang.Object
  edu.cmu.sei.arche.vo.CoreFact
      edu.cmu.sei.arche.vo.RelationshipVO
public class RelationshipVO
extends CoreFact

Corresponds to different facts in ArchE Core. The core fact type corresponds to the id of the RelationshipTypeVO that is a property of the this relationship vo. Examples of core facts that are relationships:

  • MAIN::SequenceRelation
  • MAIN::ResponsibilityToResponsibilityRelation
  • MAIN::ResponsibilityRefinementRelation
In all these facts, the relationship is a relationship between responsibilitys iff both elements being related (aka parent and child, or lhs and rhs) are responsibilities.

All relationship facts in the core have at least the following slots that are used to fill the VO properties:

  • source
  • parent
  • child

Author:
Paulo Merson
